Step 1 - Create an instance and bucket on any cloud provider.

Step 2 - Now congigure it by giving Access key , Secret access key and starting that instance in any local terminal.
(Windows - Nomachine/Mobaxterm/Putty)
(Mac - iTerm2)
(Linux - Linux terminal)

Step 3 - Create an sample file in bash (Here i have created "aws_resource_tracker.sh").

Step 4 - Write the script in bash to automate the process .

Step 5 - Now just give the permissions by chmod(permission should be as per your convenience)

Step 6 - Now just run this scripts and there you go , your ready to automate the following -
#list s3 buckets
#list EC2 instances
#list lambda
#list IAM users.

